<p><b>Zarathos</b> (<span class="rt-commentedText nowrap"><small><a href="/wiki/British_English" title="British English">UK</a>: </small><span class="IPA nopopups noexcerpt"><a href="/wiki/Help:IPA/English" title="Help:IPA/English">/<span style="border-bottom:1px dotted"><span title="/ˈ/: primary stress follows">ˈ</span><span title="&#39;z&#39; in &#39;zoom&#39;">z</span><span title="/ær/: &#39;arr&#39; in &#39;marry&#39;">ær</span><span title="/ə/: &#39;a&#39; in &#39;about&#39;">ə</span><span title="/θ/: &#39;th&#39; in &#39;thigh&#39;">θ</span><span title="/ɒ/: &#39;o&#39; in &#39;body&#39;">ɒ</span><span title="&#39;s&#39; in &#39;sigh&#39;">s</span></span>/</a></span></span>, <span class="rt-commentedText nowrap"><small><a href="/wiki/American_English" title="American English">US</a>: </small><span class="IPA nopopups noexcerpt"><a href="/wiki/Help:IPA/English" title="Help:IPA/English">/-<span style="border-bottom:1px dotted"><span title="/θ/: &#39;th&#39; in &#39;thigh&#39;">θ</span><span title="/oʊ/: &#39;o&#39; in &#39;code&#39;">oʊ</span><span title="&#39;s&#39; in &#39;sigh&#39;">s</span></span>/</a></span></span>) is a <a href="/wiki/Fictional_character" class="mw-redirect" title="Fictional character">fictional character</a> appearing in <a href="/wiki/American_comic_book" title="American comic book">American comic books</a> published by <a href="/wiki/Marvel_Comics" title="Marvel Comics">Marvel Comics</a>. He is depicted usually as a villain in stories featuring the character <a href="/wiki/Ghost_Rider" title="Ghost Rider">Ghost Rider</a>. A <a href="/wiki/List_of_Marvel_Comics_demons" title="List of Marvel Comics demons">demonic being</a> who tortures and devours souls, he first appeared in  <i><a href="/wiki/Marvel_Spotlight" title="Marvel Spotlight">Marvel Spotlight</a></i> #5 (August 1972), and was created by writers <a href="/wiki/Roy_Thomas" title="Roy Thomas">Roy Thomas</a> and <a href="/wiki/Gary_Friedrich" title="Gary Friedrich">Gary Friedrich</a>, and artist <a href="/wiki/Mike_Ploog" title="Mike Ploog">Mike Ploog</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
